There are (2) main types of code editors

1. IDE (Integrated Development Enviroment)
    Used for whole projects, and intergrates version control, testing enviroment. etc.
    provides autocompletion within the while project, not just an open file
    Visual Studio Code is a IDE


2. Lightweight editors:
    Not as powerful as IDE but are fast and Simple

Code editors are mainly preference, there are many options to pick and choose one. it might even depend on the programming language you are using or if its paid/free 
